The paper deals with mutual information, which is a concept in information theory, and its application to gambling and information engines. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses control protocols and work extraction, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper uses analogies and mathematical methods, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
